# LSTM experiments

## wisconsin-lewis-v1

Only formatting forcings such that trained LSTMs of other regions can be used to derive predictions for these basins. No LSTM will be trained for this region.

## ontario-zhi-v1

Only formatting forcings such that trained LSTMs of other regions can be used to derive predictions for these basins. No LSTM will be trained for this region.

## grip-gl-mai-v1

Attempt to recreate GRIP-GL results using RDRS-v2 and attributes derived by Martin Gauch. Does not work because some files are missing. Martin had done hyper-parameter tuning and the following settings were best and then used for final training:
```
batch = 64
hidden = 256
learning_rate = {0:0005, 20:0.0001, 30:0.00005}
epochs = 30
dropout = 0.4
seq_length = 365
```
as found in Mai et al. (2022) Supplements and final-training/seedXXX.yml (https://github.com/julemai/GRIP-GL/blob/master/scripts/MachineLearning/final-training/seed1.yml).

## grip-gl-mai-v2

Using RDRS v2.1 and all 212 (instead of 141) basins and 2000-2018 for training.
Use setup of GRIP-GL to train 212 basins for 2000-2018 and then test for 1980-1999.
```
batch = 64
hidden = 256
learning_rate = {0:0005, 20:0.0001, 30:0.00005}
epochs = 30
dropout = 0.4
seq_length = 365
```
as found in Mai et al. (2022) Supplements and final-training/seedXXX.yml (https://github.com/julemai/GRIP-GL/blob/master/scripts/MachineLearning/final-training/seed1.yml).

## grip-gl-mai-v3

Using RDRS v2.1 and all 212 (instead of 141) basins and 2000-2018 for training.
Use setup of GRIP-GL to train 212 basins for 2000-2018 and then test for 1980-1999.
Only precipitation and temperature are used as forcings.
```
batch = 64
hidden = 256
learning_rate = {0:0005, 20:0.0001, 30:0.00005}
epochs = 30
dropout = 0.4
seq_length = 365
```
as found in Mai et al. (2022) Supplements and final-training/seedXXX.yml (https://github.com/julemai/GRIP-GL/blob/master/scripts/MachineLearning/final-training/seed1.yml).

## conus-zhi-v1

Use setup of GRIP-GL to train 513 basins for 2000-2018 and then test for 1980-1999.
```
batch = 64
hidden = 256
learning_rate = {0:0005, 20:0.0001, 30:0.00005}
epochs = 30
dropout = 0.4
seq_length = 365
```
as found in Mai et al. (2022) Supplements and final-training/seedXXX.yml (https://github.com/julemai/GRIP-GL/blob/master/scripts/MachineLearning/final-training/seed1.yml).

## conus-zhi-v2

Same as conus-zhi-v2 but using hyper-parameters from Gauch et al. (2021) for MTS-LSTM:
```
batch = 256
hidden = 256
learning_rate = {0:001, 10:0.0005, 25:0.0001}
epochs = 30
dropout = 0.4
seq_length = 365
```
as found in Gauch et al. (2021) HESS in Tab. D1.
